values: is everything really the way i think it is?

merry christmas
happy new year.

i reallly need a new year. this one sucked hugely bad

.my mind is gone.

so for the most part everything has gotten better. 

i had a giggily day today.

work was work and was lame like always, but i ate good free food.

sitting outside of the train station before i walk to my internship made my day. 
This homeless guy just starts growling, and saying "what what" to/at absolutly no one.

oh yeah and before that swillis had this silly site posted in his profile. the stupidest thing ever but it made me giggle a ton.
http://www.cryingwhileeating.com/

then when i was waiting for my train back home i made friends with Craig. the homless guy, really nice, and really really really drunk. he wouldn't stop talking to me but it was cool. he told me to stay in school, asked me how old i was like 7 times, told me i was pretty, almost started crying, offered me alcohol and i refused to take it- he asked me that like 3 times, a whole bunch of stuff.

then while i'm still waiting for my train, but trying to get abreak from craig for a min, this kid askes me for any spare change coz someoen stole his train ticket or something. so i gave him $6.

THEN i come home. have an awesome good lovey dovey phone call with Trevor

Then i end up hanging out with Pirelli for about 2 hours, just driving around doing nothing but laughing and telling stories. haha i love that "older brother" of mine. I love it. he's cute, but we have been friends fo soo long that we don;t even remotly like eachother that way. :) we can hang out and do whatever and there is no attraction or lust or anything! so he is pretty much a girl to me. i love it! :) he is aweosme. 

i think i will always be confused about everything. :/

and now i am going to sleep, coz i have a massivly busy day tomorrow that starts at 7am. I'll be in boston for most of it, but the sucky thing is is that i have no clue when i'm going to get home, i know the earliest i'll get back to franktown is at 730pm, but i made plans to hang out with trevor tomorrow, but i don't know if i'll have time. i have to work, and intern, and go to school for a lecture. awesome.  i guess we'll see.

oh yeah.... movie day / night whatever on saturday??! anyone else in?? maybe order some EXTRA LARGE pizzas??? hmmm?? ya wanna?? yesssss

k. bye.

happy late birthday Mikey and John!
wuv you boiz. :P




so.. This week has sucked. last week sucked. i hope next week doesn't suck.
trevor and i.. i dunno anymore. makes stina sad. 

all work and no play make stina hate everything. :)

i just don't know wut to do.
I'm back in a rut, but this time i might be stuck there for a while alone.

last night was my sisters' Jack and Jill party. Pretty fun. drunk people and my dad are silly.

Lydie found out she is going to have a baby boy!!! 

on top of everything i have bone problems again. I have to go see the doc on thursday. FUN. 

umm. yup. i'm bored. welp see ya later.

OMYGOODNESS i can't stop thinking about it. haha AHHHHH crazy!! :)

There is a baby in my room right now crying.
i need a friggen ciggarette.

It all started yesterday @ My nephew's b-day party. The poor kid had too much junk food to eat and i picked him up and hugged him. He started crying his eyes out for soo long, then he threw up all over my sister. I was so embarrased. I felt so bad. THEN Anthony wants to go into boston and go over Pat's apartment and he wants Trevor and I to go with him. I didn;t really want to go, but i ended up going anyways. So we take the train in at 6:30. On the Train I was getting a little aggitated with Trevor, but nothing big. When we got there we had to walk about 25 min. to his place. No one was there besides Pat and his roomate Sam, and Trevor, Anthony, Hopper and I just sat around for a while. Once it was time for us to leave everyone else showed up. So we leave his place at 11pm. the train we needed to catch is at 11:20. We got a little lost, then found the Orange line which we waited for for like 15 minutes. THE ORANGE LINE SUCKS. That was the last train out, so we got stuck in boston for the night. So we start walking back to Pats place and we firgure we can take a cab all the way back to franklin for $80. We didn't do that but later regreted it. SO we go to the Bk Lounge to get some food and while we are eating everyone in there turned towards the window and was talking about someone getting shot like right outside BK. I didn;t hear anything, but when we were leaving we saw the whole crime scene tape up and cops everywhere. So after that we took a cab back to Pats. (firt time i ever rode in a taxi by the way) We got there and then had to wait outside for him for 20 mins. But Jeff Paul and lynch came by so that was good. Soo Trevor and I are exhausted when we get up stairs and go right to bed. WE SLEPT IN A FUCKING CLOSET. HARD WOOD FLOOR. my sweatshirt and Trevor's sweatshirt were are pillows. At least we were lucky enough to get a blanket from Pat. Yup. deffinatly couldn't sleep. well I could a little, but Trevor didn't get much sleep. I was pretty drunk so i just passed out. SO yup. hahah um... we are gonna skip the next part coz it's stupid and embarassing.. (haha ok...i peed myslef again. stupid beer)(OH YEAH I COMPLETLY FORGOT.. NAK IF YOU ARE READING THIS... when we were walking to Pat's we have to walk by Berkley haha and all i could think of was being stupid and saying " WHAT'S UP SEE YOU IN CLASS"  :) haha ) SO we wake up at 6:30am. We attempt to take a cab to the train but no one would stop for us. so we get to the Orange line and we wait forever and a year again for the fricken orange line. SOOO we get to the train station and were all set to take the 7:20am Franklin Train. THERE IS NO FREAKING 7:20am train. The earliest train that goes to Franklin on Sunday is 11:20. We read the schedule wrong. TREVOR AND I HAD TO GO TO WORK. I was suppose to work at 7:30am and he had to work at 8. i had to call out even though there is no one to replace me, and he had to call them and tell them he'd be there later. TREVOR AND I GOT STUCK WALKING AROUND BOSTON FOR 4 AND A HALF HOURS. It was freazing, we were both exhausted, my feet and knees were killing me, BUT on the other hand it was kinda nice. Atleast the sun was out and we were together and not alone.  SO after we walk for an hour, We go to a different BK lounge and get cheap breakfast. I was so hungry, but that just made my stomache ache a lil. THEN we finally have an hour left till our Train comes. We are sitting in the Back Bay Train Station and Trevor is sleeping, I'm trying to make myself comfortable, and i'm not smiling. This really nice sweet old lady comes over to me and asks us if we are ok, and if we are sick and need any money. hahah She was so sweet, and then trevor wakes up in the midst of all that and the lady starts crying. She said are u sure u guys are ok, U (trevor) look just like my son, a spitting image. He passed away 2 years ago. Then she turns and walks away crying, and we are both like.. ummmm wut can we do? she was so sweet tho. THEN Trevor is in the bathroom and i'm waiting for him outside.I see this old guy at the bathroom mirror with a cane and a huge gash on his head. He's looking threw the TRASH for paper towels for his head. Trevor asks him if he is ok and the guy says. I just fell on the escelator. the guy had a concussion I guess and was bleeding everywhere so trevor told the commuterrail people and they were getting him an ambulance. Then our Train comes and we get to go home. It was a very uncomfortable ride, but we finally got home around 1pm. And the whole time I was in Boston i needed a tampon soo bad and i didn't have one. it sucked. I was never so excited in my life to be home and to be able to take a shower. :)  
Now I am going to take a very long nap. :)

You prefer your romance and love to wild and daring rather than typical or boring, you would rather pursue than be pursued and, when it comes to physical love, your satisfaction comes more from providing a wonderful time to your partner than simply seeking your own.

This places you in the Lover Style of: The Liberated Lover.

The Liberated Lover is a wonderful Lover Style, and forms the kind of free-thinking, sexually-exciting, self-confident lover that society once condemned but that a liberal-mind cherishes and exults. The Liberated Lover is a treasure to find, though it can sometimes be difficult to do so because they are often already engaged in relationships or are in high-demand if "in the market."

In terms of physical love, the Liberated Lover is possibly the most thrilling and demanding of all, with the one potential drawback being that it is possible to feel 'overmatched' at times by their prowess and selfless giving. Given trust and understanding, and the right lover, the Liberated Lover can be a delight in bed.
